The paper deals with the design of FPT algorithms, which is a topic in computational complexity theory. The algorithmic techniques used in the paper involve connections among various fields such as constraints satisfaction, combinatorial optimization, and LP relaxations. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper also involves graph theory and optimization, which are covered by sub-categories cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
